FBIS4-59113 "drnes091bb_94001" FBIS-NES-94-091 Daily Report 7 May 1994 Inter-Arab Affairs Oil Minister Addresses Arab Energy Conference Oil Minister Addresses Arab Energy Conference JN0805082094 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in Arabic 1815 GMT 7 May 94 JN0805082094 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network Arabic BFN [Excerpts] The fifth Arab Energy Conference began in Cairo today. Arab oil and energy ministers, in addition to the ministers of electricity in the five countries to be linked by a single grid, are participating. These countries are Syria, Egypt, Jordan, Iraq, and Turkey. [passage omitted] In a speech he delivered for Syria, Dr. Nadir al-Nabulis, minister of oil and mineral resources, said Syria under President Hafiz al-Asad has succeeded in establishing a developed economy and has attained many achievements in the oil and natural gas industry. [passage omitted] Dr. al-Nabulsi said that the imposition of taxes on oil on the pretext of the safety of the environment is not based on clear scientific foundations. [passage omitted]
